gomodel:SYNGO_3663  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Electrophysiology evidences showed that LTD of NMDAR EPSCs is blocked by a peptide that inhibits cofilin-1.\n\n29/5/2017 Pim\n-Cofilin dom.neg. phospho-peptide was traced back to sequence MASGVAVSDGVIKVFN via PMID:15572107. Blast on uniprot website showed two ungapped hits in rat sequences (P45592(cofilin); A0A0G2KA35(partial cofilin clone in TrEMBL)). The peptide therefore can be regarded seen as specific for cofilin 1.\n- Uniprot states for cofillin-1: \"Binds to F-actin and exhibits pH-sensitive F-actin depolymerizing activity\" Since cofillin itself is known to exhibit actin-depolymerase activity, I have left the \"regulates....\" modification of synaptic structure uncheck since I reasoned that cofilin is performing the structure modification itself.\n- Fig.6 shows that loading of postsynaptic neurons with a a phosphorylated cofilin peptide bloacked LTD of NMDAR EPSCs.. Experimental description: Sprague-Dawley rats (3-4 weeks old)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3663" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

